    <stitle>CE 200, CE 300 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - Brake Pedal</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Brake Pedal</title>
        <para>The brake pedal assembly is mounted to the steering column mounting bracket. The pivot bar assembly is
            mounted behind the steering column shaft and is easily removed.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900974" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900974.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 80. Brake Pedal Attachment Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BRAKE PEDAL PIVOT BAR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. PIVOT BAR MOUNTING NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BRAKE ROD RETAINER PIN AND CLIP</callout1>
                <callout1>4. COWL REINFORCING MOUNTING PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>5. BRAKE PEDAL ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>6. STEERING COLUMN SHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>7. STEERING COLUMN MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the retainer pin and clip on the brake pedal arm (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900974">Figure 80, Item 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retainer clip and push out the retainer pin from brake pedal arm.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove mounting nut (
                <hotlnk document="s09009_60.xml" xrefid="f0900975">Figure 106, Item 3</hotlnk>) securing the pivot bar
                on the steering column mounting bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900974">Figure 80, Item 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With retainer pin and clip removed from brake rod, pull pedal assembly forward to clear
                brake rod clevis (
                <hotlnk document="s09009_60.xml" xrefid="f0900975">Figure 106, Items 1 and 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolt securing the brake pedal pivot bar.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pivot bar and brake pedal assembly out of position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the nylon bushing on each side pivot bar assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the nylon bushing for any damage or distortion, replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
